# AerospikeService

The AerospikeService gem has been installed. Here's what to do next:

## Configuration

A configuration file has been created at:
  config/aerospike_service.yml

Review this file and update it with your Aerospike connection settings.

An initializer has also been created at:
  config/initializers/aerospike_service.rb

This initializer loads the configuration and sets up the service.

## Basic Usage

```ruby
# Get a value
user_data = AerospikeService.get("user:123")

# Store a value
AerospikeService.put("user:123", { name: "John Doe", email: "john@example.com" })

# Delete a value
AerospikeService.delete("user:123")

# Check if a key exists
if AerospikeService.exists?("user:123")
  # Do something
end

# Increment a counter
AerospikeService.increment("counter:visits", "count", 1)
```

## Namespace Shortcuts

To create convenient shortcuts for your namespaces, run:

```bash
$ rails generate aerospike_service:shortcuts
```

This will create a module that lets you access specific namespaces directly:

```ruby
# Access the 'users' namespace
Aerospike::Users.get("123")
Aerospike::Users.put("123", { name: "John Doe" })

# Access the 'analytics' namespace
Aerospike::Analytics.increment("daily:visits", "count")
```

## Documentation

For more information, see the gem documentation at:
https://github.com/your-org/infrastructure_services/tree/main/aerospike